# REAL CHEMISTRY: WATER ICHOR → HYDROGEN + OXYGEN
# (Mineral ichor SiO2 is inert and does not react)

# Electrolysis of water:
2 H2O(l)  →  2 H2(g)  +  O2(g)

# In an ichor mixture:
SiO2(s) + 2 H2O(l)  →  SiO2(s) + 2 H2(g) + O2(g)

# Notes:
# - Only H2O decomposes.
# - SiO2 remains unchanged.
# - Dissolved ions (Na+, Ca2+, Cl-, SO4^2-, NO3-) act as electrolytes.
